You remember the story
of Private Philippe?

353
00:42:29,093 --> 00:42:32,654
Jacques, tell Camille.
He doesn't know it.

354
00:42:41,505 --> 00:42:42,631
Tell him!

355
00:43:00,524 --> 00:43:03,755
It's the story of a soldier
called Philippe.

356
00:43:03,895 --> 00:43:05,157
He's twenty.

357
00:43:06,530 --> 00:43:09,158
He's been fighting
for eighteen months.

358
00:43:15,740 --> 00:43:18,174
Before the war,
he was young and handsome,

359
00:43:18,309 --> 00:43:19,970
with blue eyes.

360
00:43:22,780 --> 00:43:24,270
He has a pretty sister.

361
00:43:24,782 --> 00:43:26,079
Alice.

362
00:43:26,918 --> 00:43:29,352
He has shown her photo
to all the others.

363
00:43:31,589 --> 00:43:33,113
She is blond,

364
00:43:33,658 --> 00:43:37,253
with blue eyes,
blue as the ocean's depths.

365
00:43:42,033 --> 00:43:44,558
He often writes long letters to her.

366
00:43:44,936 --> 00:43:46,528
He loves his sister.

367
00:43:52,009 --> 00:43:53,977
Letters that say things like:

368
00:43:54,278 --> 00:43:55,506
"Alice,

369
00:43:56,247 --> 00:43:58,511
"It was a beautiful day today.

370
00:43:59,250 --> 00:44:02,117
"The moon was shining in the sky
at five p.m.

371
00:44:03,354 --> 00:44:06,721
"It's odd
but that's what happened.

372
00:44:10,261 --> 00:44:13,389
"The birds sang all day
but then fell silent

373
00:44:14,031 --> 00:44:16,124
"'when night started to fall."

374
00:44:20,404 --> 00:44:22,668
He certainly knows how to write.

375
00:44:22,807 --> 00:44:24,240
Not like us.

376
00:44:24,375 --> 00:44:26,673
Well, I don't mean you, Antoine.

377
00:44:27,678 --> 00:44:31,011
In real life, he's a student.
A history student.

378
00:44:33,084 --> 00:44:35,109
He loves Greek history.

379
00:44:35,252 --> 00:44:37,083
He always talks about it.

380
00:44:38,155 --> 00:44:40,783
He loves giving details about it.

381
00:44:40,925 --> 00:44:43,621
He can translate anything into Greek.

382
00:44:47,431 --> 00:44:50,923
He has a passion: Atlantis.

383
00:44:59,810 --> 00:45:01,141
He loves to sleep.

384
00:45:02,046 --> 00:45:06,005
Some love to eat or drink.
He loves to sleep.

385
00:45:06,884 --> 00:45:08,784
In any case, he needs to sleep.

386
00:45:13,024 --> 00:45:15,618
You can't sleep when you want
in a war.

387
00:45:16,961 --> 00:45:20,488
He gets woken in the middle
of the night or at dawn.

388
00:45:20,631 --> 00:45:23,464
He sleeps three hours,
then has to get up.

389
00:45:23,601 --> 00:45:26,502
Two hours, then he has to get up...

390
00:45:29,106 --> 00:45:32,234
Sometimes, he doesn't sleep
for two or three days.

391
00:45:32,810 --> 00:45:34,004
It makes him ill.

392
00:45:38,682 --> 00:45:40,809
That's what Philippe is like.

393
00:45:42,987 --> 00:45:44,511
Then, little by little,

394
00:45:47,725 --> 00:45:51,923
he talks less and less
about Atlantis.

395
00:45:56,200 --> 00:46:00,261
He says he's not interested.
He doesn't want to talk about it.

396
00:46:01,338 --> 00:46:03,135
He says none of it is any use.

397
00:46:07,678 --> 00:46:11,114
Even when we ask him questions,
he refuses...

398
00:46:12,616 --> 00:46:14,083
to answer them.

399
00:46:17,254 --> 00:46:20,382
He can't sleep.
He won't talk about the Greeks.

400
00:46:22,960 --> 00:46:24,791
He even stops writing to Alice.

401
00:46:29,066 --> 00:46:32,695
Little by little, he talks
less and less about Atlantis.

402
