01:02:56,853 --> 01:02:57,979
Cut it out!

551
01:03:43,133 --> 01:03:44,225
I can't feel my leg!

552
01:04:13,129 --> 01:04:14,460
Help!

553
01:04:23,606 --> 01:04:25,005
Help!

554
01:05:03,746 --> 01:05:04,678
Get up!

555
01:06:04,440 --> 01:06:06,032
We heard you shouting.

556
01:06:07,243 --> 01:06:08,801
You're lucky.

557
01:06:09,679 --> 01:06:11,806
Not many people pass this way.

558
01:06:14,284 --> 01:06:16,275
My name's Elias.

559
01:06:16,419 --> 01:06:18,114
This is my son.

560
01:06:22,392 --> 01:06:23,859
Lieutenant Paulhan,

561
01:06:23,993 --> 01:06:27,224
80th infantry regiment,
12th company.

562
01:06:29,565 --> 01:06:31,055
Where are you going?

563
01:06:33,670 --> 01:06:35,399
What are you doing here?

564
01:06:43,279 --> 01:06:44,803
Thank you for your help.

565
01:06:49,886 --> 01:06:51,581
We'll look after them.

566
01:06:52,789 --> 01:06:54,017
Follow me.

567
01:07:02,765 --> 01:07:05,325
You don't want to talk.
You must be tired.

568
01:07:05,468 --> 01:07:07,163
Everyone is tired here.

569
01:07:08,905 --> 01:07:12,341
We know what it means
to be tired too.

570
01:07:12,809 --> 01:07:15,471
Sometimes,
we don't want to talk either.

571
01:07:16,179 --> 01:07:17,578
My dad and I

572
01:07:18,715 --> 01:07:20,478
will look after you,

573
01:07:21,617 --> 01:07:23,209
we'll feed you

574
01:07:23,853 --> 01:07:26,822
and everything will be fine after,
you'll see.

575
01:07:28,191 --> 01:07:30,421
Try to rest now.

576
01:07:40,036 --> 01:07:41,094
Thank you.

577
01:07:52,749 --> 01:07:55,650
It must have been good here
before the war.

578
01:08:06,195 --> 01:08:07,560
Me and my son

579
01:08:08,631 --> 01:08:10,531
can only come after dark.

580
01:08:12,268 --> 01:08:14,532
Otherwise,
the locals might see us

581
01:08:14,670 --> 01:08:17,161
and then they'll denounce you.

582
01:08:20,510 --> 01:08:21,807
Denounce us?

583
01:08:25,148 --> 01:08:27,480
I saw right away you were deserters.

584
01:08:31,854 --> 01:08:33,082
How?

585
01:08:35,191 --> 01:08:37,352
By the state of your uniforms.

586
01:08:38,494 --> 01:08:40,359
And the number of you.

587
01:08:41,731 --> 01:08:44,928
And your cadet too.
He talked to my son.

588
01:08:47,270 --> 01:08:49,295
He spoke about your journey.

589
01:08:51,874 --> 01:08:53,273
And about things...

590
01:08:54,644 --> 01:08:56,441
Things that you have seen.

591
01:08:58,080 --> 01:08:59,604
He isn't very smart.

592
01:09:03,286 --> 01:09:05,686
There's the look on your face too.

593
01:09:08,991 --> 01:09:10,288
What look?

594
01:09:13,329 --> 01:09:15,695
I won't say. Ill only scare you.

595
01:09:21,270 --> 01:09:23,397
What do you risk by hiding us?

596
01:09:24,740 --> 01:09:26,765
A lot. But it doesn't matter.

597
01:09:27,410 --> 01:09:29,401
You've done so much for us.

598
01:09:31,013 --> 01:09:33,504
I have one favour left to ask of you.

599
01:09:37,053 --> 01:09:40,284
Could you send

600
01:09:42,725 --> 01:09:46,923
my dog tag to this address?

601
01:09:48,197 --> 01:09:51,166
It's for my superior.
It's very important.

602
01:09:51,701 --> 01:09:53,566
He'll know what it means.

603
01:09:54,770 --> 01:09:56,135
Yes, I'll do it.

604
01:09:59,375 --> 01:10:01,843
I'll bring you local maps tomorrow.

605
01:10:02,578 --> 01:10:04,068
You have to be careful.

606
01:12:29,859 --> 01:12:31,156
Alfred!

607
01:12:34,263 --> 01:12:35,491
Camille...

608
01:13:00,523 --> 01:13:02,013
My son!

609
01:15:23,299 --> 01:15:26,166
Shit, they'll find the bodies.

610
01:16:28,197 --> 01:16:31,132
I'm Camille Robin,
wife of François Robin.

611
01:16:32,902 --> 01:16:35,268
François is like you.
He's a soldier.

612
01:16:37,406 --> 01:16:39,874
When I met him,
he had an open smile.

613
01:16:40,910 --> 01:16:43,003
Not a smile like yours, Alfred.

614
01:16:43,979 --> 01:16:46,140
Not like yours either, Antoine.

615
01:16:49,251 --> 01:16:52,084
An open smile
like someone without worries.

616
01:17:01,664 --> 01:17:03,825
On our wedding day, I was sick,

617
01:17:04,667 --> 01:17:06,635
so sick I could hardly stand.

618
01:17:07,202 --> 01:17:10,035
People kept saying
the bride looked odd.

619
01:17:10,606 --> 01:17:13,575
I told myself
that I had to last the day out,

620
01:17:14,176 --> 01:17:16,007
that I could collapse after,

621
01:17:16,145 --> 01:17:18,136
but that I had to keep going.

622
01:17:23,585 --> 01:17:27,453
That evening, François said
I'd never been more beautiful.

623
01:17:32,695 --> 01:17:35,892
You've no idea
how happy I was with my husband.

624
01:17:38,834 --> 01:17:41,200
My sister was even a bit jealous.

625
01:17:48,544 --> 01:17:50,705
When he left, he wrote often,

626
01:17:51,246 --> 01:17:53,009
as often as he could.

627
01:17:55,050 --> 01:17:56,449
And then nothing.

628
01:18:02,424 --> 01:18:03,789
I waited.

629
01:18:03,926 --> 01:18:05,416
I didn't worry.

630
01:18:07,429 --> 01:18:09,090
And then I had a letter.

631
01:18:10,532 --> 01:18:13,933
"Camille, I don't want you
to write back to me.

632
01:18:14,470 --> 01:18:17,166
"You'll never see me again.
François."

633
01:18:18,807 --> 01:18:20,104
That was all.

634
01:18:21,577 --> 01:18:24,569
He's been badly advised.
He's been misled.

635
01:18:25,848 --> 01:18:27,509
He must have nightmares.

636
01:18:29,451 --> 01:18:31,612
I bet he wrote after a nightmare.

637
01:18:34,089 --> 01:18:35,784
The nights are cold.

638
01:18:36,325 --> 01:18:38,190
You can't think straight.

639
01:18:39,762 --> 01:18:41,855
The noise of the front is scary too.

640
01:18:44,967 --> 01:18:47,435
You never know
what tomorrow will bring.

641
01:18:49,505 --> 01:18:51,769
The war has come between us.

642
01:18:54,943 --> 01:18:56,535
But once it is over,

643
01:18:57,613 --> 01:19:01,549
once I find François again,
once he sees he was wrong...

644
01:19:01,717 --> 01:19:03,480
Are you an orphan though?

645
01:19:05,020 --> 01:19:05,918
No.

646
01:19:07,356 --> 01:19:10,189
Not even?
I feel like smashing your face in.

647
01:19:11,560 --> 01:19:14,552
You must love your husband a lot
to do this.

648
01:19:15,497 --> 01:19:16,623
Yes.

649
01:19:16,832 --> 01:19:18,697
Sure you love him that much?

650
01:19:19,001 --> 01:19:20,059
Yes.

651
01:19:23,572 --> 01:19:24,630
I didn't fool you.

652
01:19:27,042 --> 01:19:29,272
And now, Camille...

653
01:19:30,279 --> 01:19:31,974
What do you plan to do?

654
01:19:34,716 --> 01:19:35,910
I don't know.

655
01:19:37,920 --> 01:19:39,581
I don't know where he is,

656
01:19:39,721 --> 01:19:41,655
if he's dead or alive.

657
01:19:44,726 --> 01:19:46,023
So I'm following you.

658
01:19:46,695 --> 01:19:49,129
That way, I feel as if I'm with him.

659
01:19:52,134 --> 01:19:55,331
Camille told you a tall story, true,

660
01:19:55,471 --> 01:19:57,735
but that's no reason to change.

661
01:19:59,408 --> 01:20:02,434
Everything must stay like before.

662
01:20:02,578 --> 01:20:04,569
For you too, Camille.

663
01:20:06,648 --> 01:20:08,445
Keep your male clothing.

664
01:20:12,521 --> 01:20:14,546
If you get yourself noticed,

665
01:20:15,891 --> 01:20:17,586
we could get caught.

666
01:20:19,428 --> 01:20:21,225
My sole concern

667
01:20:21,363 --> 01:20:23,888
is to get us to Holland
safe and sound.

668
01:20:25,734 --> 01:20:28,601
You're just as full of infamy
as we are.

669
01:20:56,298 --> 01:20:59,233
Camille, I can help you too.

670
01:21:40,542 --> 01:21:42,874
Wait here, I'll fetch the cadet!

671
01:21:55,457 --> 01:21:56,685
I can't see him.

672
01:21:56,825 --> 01:21:58,656
We can't stay here. Let's go!

673
01:23:33,322 --> 01:23:34,812
Here lies Thibault Marin,

674
01:23:34,956 --> 01:23:36,355
alias "the cadet"'.

675
01:23:37,826 --> 01:23:39,350
May he rest in peace.

676
01:23:53,742 --> 01:23:55,903
He's waiting for us in Atlantis,

677
01:23:56,044 --> 01:23:57,170
in Holland,

678
01:23:57,312 --> 01:24:00,179
wherever there are orphans
full of infamy.

679
01:26:00,635 --> 01:26:03,502
I, the blind girl

680
01:26:04,539 --> 01:26:06,632
I'll tell you one last time

681
01:26:06,775 --> 01:26:09,710
Put your head on my shoulder

682
01:26:10,579 --> 01:26:13,173
You Pole, there's a room

683
01:26:13,315 --> 01:26:18,184
Where I'll tell you all my secrets

684
01:26:18,720 --> 01:26:21,917
It's my bedroom so come to me

685
01:26:22,324 --> 01:26:25,816
It's dark, I'm alone

686
01:26:25,961 --> 01:26:28,521
And I won't be afraid

687
01:26:28,663 --> 01:26:31,063
I love the way you dress

688
01:26:31,199 --> 01:26:35,829
I'd like France to be invaded
by Poland

689
01:26:35,971 --> 01:26:38,371
I feel pleasant vibrations

690
01:26:38,507 --> 01:26:39,701
Close my eyes

691
01:26:40,642 --> 01:26:43,406
You seem much closer now

692
01:26:43,545 --> 01:26:46,537
I must keep these vibrations of love

693
01:26:46,748 --> 01:26:48,238
I have seen many things

694
01:26:48,383 --> 01:26:52,479
But Poland is what I prefer

695
01:26:59,194 --> 01:27:01,856
If you leave me, I'll never

696
01:27:03,064 --> 01:27:04,929
Feel these vibrations again

697
01:27:05,100 --> 01:27:07,864
It may be the influence
of the seasons

698
01:27:09,104 --> 01:27:11,572
How could I know?

699
01:27:11,873 --> 01:27:16,867
This morning, I opened the shutters

700
01:27:17,312 --> 01:27:22,579
You were looking at my belly again

701
01:27:23,818 --> 01:27:26,685
I had no time to promise you anything

702
01:27:26,855 --> 01:27:29,585
I love the way you dress

703
01:27:29,724 --> 01:27:34,457
I'd like France to be invaded
by Poland

704
01:27:34,596 --> 01:27:37,190
I feel pleasant vibrations

705
01:27:37,332 --> 01:27:38,526
Close my eyes

706
01:27:39,234 --> 01:27:41,998
You seem much closer now

707
01:27:42,137 --> 01:27:45,038
I must keep these vibrations of love

708
01:27:45,273 --> 01:27:47,002
I have seen many things

709
01:27:47,142 --> 01:27:51,078
But Poland is what I prefer

710
01:27:57,519 --> 01:28:00,283
You mustn't feel ashamed

711
01:28:01,389 --> 01:28:03,482
No, no, don't worry

712
01:28:03,625 --> 01:28:06,753
It wasn't your bedroom

713
01:28:07,696 --> 01:28:10,062
And it wasn't your country

714
01:28:10,332 --> 01:28:13,062
If I needed him

715
01:28:13,201 --> 01:28:16,102
Would he come to me?

716
01:28:16,905 --> 01:28:19,703
Would he come to me?

717
01:28:19,841 --> 01:28:22,969
Would he come to me?

718
01:28:23,111 --> 01:28:25,944
Would he come to me?

719
01:28:26,081 --> 01:28:30,017
Would he come to me?

720
01:29:17,832 --> 01:29:19,424
Where have you come from?

721
01:29:20,435 --> 01:29:21,959
From Beverloo.

722
01:29:22,537 --> 01:29:24,596
Let me by. I've done no harm.

723
01:29:26,541 --> 01:29:28,008
Beverloo?

724
01:29:29,444 --> 01:29:31,810
It's a prison camp in Belgium.

725
01:29:33,281 --> 01:29:34,805
I escaped.

726
01:29:36,918 --> 01:29:38,545
Where are you going?

727
01:29:39,654 --> 01:29:41,451
I'm going back to my country.

728
01:29:41,890 --> 01:29:43,187
France.

729
01:29:44,959 --> 01:29:46,051
And then?

730
01:29:48,530 --> 01:29:49,690
Then?

731
01:29:50,765 --> 01:29:52,096
I don't know.

732
01:30:00,608 --> 01:30:01,666
Get up.

733
01:30:03,511 --> 01:30:04,808
I can't.

734
01:30:05,747 --> 01:30:07,237
I'm too tired.

735
01:30:08,216 --> 01:30:09,444
Get up.

736
01:30:12,854 --> 01:30:14,822
What do you know of my life?

737
01:30:19,594 --> 01:30:21,027
Stop complaining.

738
01:30:23,865 --> 01:30:25,799
Why are you crying, François?

739
01:30:28,103 --> 01:30:30,196
It's because my eyes hurt.

740
01:30:51,526 --> 01:30:52,754
Camille...

741
01:30:56,698 --> 01:30:57,995
Wait here.

742
01:31:08,576 --> 01:31:09,804
Well?

743
01:31:13,248 --> 01:31:15,079
I already told you.

744
01:31:15,216 --> 01:31:16,706
What?

745
01:31:18,119 --> 01:31:20,053
You just want to die.

746
01:31:22,023 --> 01:31:23,081
No.

747
01:31:23,858 --> 01:31:25,723
I wanted to find my husband.

748
01:31:27,028 --> 01:31:28,962
It's the same thing.

749
01:31:30,398 --> 01:31:32,389
We won't say goodbye, Camille.

750
01:32:55,149 --> 01:32:56,639
Slowly, François.

751
01:32:57,952 --> 01:32:59,385
Be more gentle.

752
01:33:01,389 --> 01:33:02,549
All right.

753
01:33:42,297 --> 01:33:43,696
Alfred...

754
01:33:44,732 --> 01:33:45,596
Jean...

755
01:33:47,068 --> 01:33:48,592
Antoine...

756
01:34:41,089 --> 01:34:46,356
The lieutenant and his men
never reached Holland.

757
